description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for Band 6 scrub practitioners in our Orthopaedic Theatre department, Working between Broomfield and Braintree Community Hopspitals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, dynamic and self motivate qualified registered nurses and ODPs to join our friendly Scrub Team here at Mid Essex Hospital Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidate should have an aptitude to lead the team and have good management skills to co-ordinate and represent the theatre department in the absence of the senior management team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a key member of the team, you are responsible to deliver high standards of patient care and have the ability to support and develop theatre practitioners to facilitate on excellent care within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate may be expected to work across all specialties. As we are a large department our staff have the opportunity to work in day, bank holidays and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMary AllenJob titleSenior Sister Ortho TheatresEmail addressmary.allen@meht.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
